  "prompt": "What are two water source?",
  "response": "Two common sources of water are:\n\n1. Surface Water: This includes rivers, lakes, streams, reservoirs, and oceans. Surface water is typically collected and treated before being used for drinking, agriculture, and industrial purposes.\n\n2. Groundwater: This is water found underground in aquifers, which are geological formations of soil, sand, and rocks that can store and yield water. Groundwater is accessed through wells and is often used for drinking water and irrigation.\n\nBoth sources are essential for meeting various human, agricultural, and industrial needs.",
